docs.text: in 1987 the stock market crashed , and oliver stone's wall street was released to critical acclaim and packed movie houses .

docs.text: wall street lucked out in its timing ; the recent crash gave the film a resonation it might not of had , and though its kill-or-be-killed approach to business was exaggerated , that very ideology was keyed into the mind set of the quintessential reagan-era businessman .
